**Virat Kohli** is an Indian international cricketer and the former captain of the Indian national team. He is widely regarded as one of the greatest batsmen in the history of the sport and one of the most famous athletes in the world.

Here is a breakdown of why he is so significant:

### 1. Cricket Career and Achievements
*   **The "King" of Batting:** Known for his incredible consistency and technique, Kohli is often referred to as "King Kohli." He is a right-handed top-order batsman.
*   **ODI Record Holder:** In 2023, he broke Sachin Tendulkar’s long-standing record for the **most centuries (100s) in One Day International (ODI) cricket**, reaching 50 centuries.
*   **World Cup Success:** He was part of the Indian team that won the **2011 ICC Cricket World Cup** and the **2024 ICC T20 World Cup**.
*   **Run Machine:** He is among the highest run-getters in the history of the game across all formats (Test, ODI, and T20I).

### 2. Leadership and Captaincy
*   Kohli served as the captain of the Indian cricket team across all formats. 
*   Under his leadership, India became a dominant force in **Test Cricket**, holding the No. 1 ranking for several years and winning a historic Test series in Australia (2018-19).
*   He is credited with transforming the culture of the Indian team by focusing heavily on **fitness, pace bowling, and an aggressive, "never-give-up" attitude.**

### 3. Playing Style
*   He is famous for being a **"Chase Master,"** having an uncanny ability to calculate and finish games when batting second.
*   His "Cover Drive" is considered one of the most aesthetically pleasing shots in the game.

### 4. Global Icon and Impact
*   **Fitness Revolution:** Kohli is often credited with changing the fitness standards of Indian cricketers, moving the team toward a more athletic and professional regime.
*   **Social Media:** He is the most-followed Asian individual on Instagram (with over 270 million followers), making him a massive global brand ambassador.
*   **IPL:** He plays for the **Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB)** in the Indian Premier League and is the all-time leading run-scorer in the tournament's history.

### 5. Personal Life
*   Born on November 5, 1988, in Delhi.
*   He is married to popular Bollywood actress **Anushka Sharma**, and the couple is frequently referred to by the media as "Virushka."

In short, Virat Kohli is more than just a cricketer; he is a cultural icon in India and a global face for the sport of cricket. He recently retired from T20 Internationals after winning the 2024 World Cup but continues to play Test and ODI cricket.
